3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo calculates DOGE/USDT funding rates using a premium index that measures the difference between perpetual and spot prices, with settlements occurring every hour. The exchange's rollup architecture enables real-time funding rate updates while keeping gas costs minimal for position adjustments. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive (perpetual trades above spot), while shorts collect payments, with the mechanism designed to keep perpetual prices aligned with underlying DOGE spot markets across major exchanges."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","DOGE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"DOGE/USDT presents compelling funding arbitrage opportunities due to meme coin sentiment cycles that create sustained directional bias and elevated funding rates. The pair's large trading volume on Aevo provides sufficient liquidity for meaningful position sizes, while hourly settlements allow traders to capitalize on shorter-term funding inefficiencies. Dogecoin's correlation with social media trends and retail sentiment often generates predictable funding rate patterns during viral market phases."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"DOGE/USDT funding rates on Aevo typically spike during meme coin rallies, with positive rates often exceeding 0.1% hourly (876% APR) during peak Elon Musk-driven hype cycles. The pair experiences extended periods of negative funding during crypto bear markets when shorts dominate, creating consistent income opportunities for long arbitrageurs. Volatility clustering around major Dogecoin announcements or Tesla integration news generates predictable funding surges that experienced traders can anticipate. Weekend funding patterns show reduced volatility as institutional participation decreases, though retail-driven meme rallies can still produce extreme rates."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's hourly funding settlements create 24 daily opportunities to capture rate differences versus 8-hour exchanges like Binance or OKX, particularly valuable during DOGE's volatile Asian and US trading sessions. Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes profitable when Aevo's rates diverge by more than 0.02% from competing venues after accounting for trading fees and slippage. The exchange's options integration allows sophisticated traders to construct delta-neutral portfolios using DOGE options to hedge perpetual positions while collecting funding payments. Funding arbitrageurs can exploit Aevo's smaller liquidity pool by taking contrarian positions when retail sentiment pushes rates to unsustainable levels."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's rollup centralization poses risks if sequencer issues prevent timely funding settlements or position liquidations during DOGE's notorious flash crashes that can exceed 20% in minutes. The exchange's smaller DOGE liquidity pool increases slippage costs for large arbitrage positions, particularly during low-volume periods when spreads widen significantly. Smart contract risks inherent to the rollup architecture could affect funding calculations or settlement mechanisms, requiring traders to monitor the protocol's technical health closely. Regulatory uncertainty around rollup-based derivatives platforms may impact long-term viability, making extended funding arbitrage strategies potentially risky for compliance-sensitive traders."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are DOGE/USDT funding rates updated on Aevo?","answer":"Funding rates update continuously based on the premium index but settle every hour. This means you can see rate changes in real-time as perpetual prices move relative to DOGE spot markets, with actual payments or collections occurring at each hourly mark."},{"question":"What makes Aevo's DOGE funding rates different from CEX rates?","answer":"Aevo's hourly settlements provide 3x more funding opportunities compared to 8-hour exchanges, while the rollup's transparent calculations eliminate concerns about rate manipulation. However, the smaller liquidity pool can create wider bid-ask spreads during volatile DOGE moves."},{"question":"Can I hedge DOGE funding positions with Aevo options?","answer":"Yes, Aevo's combined options and perpetuals platform allows you to construct delta-neutral strategies using DOGE options to hedge price risk while collecting funding payments. This is particularly effective during high-volatility periods when both funding rates and option premiums are elevated."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for profitable DOGE arbitrage on Aevo?","answer":"Given Aevo's 0.02% maker fees, profitable arbitrage typically requires funding rate differences exceeding 0.05% to cover round-trip costs and slippage. For DOGE's volatility levels, positions above $10,000 notional generally provide sufficient returns to justify the execution costs and rollup interaction fees."}]}]
